# .ai-context — Team UNTITLED | Build-it ON | FRONTEND
# ALL AI AGENTS READ THIS FIRST. THIS FILE IS LAW.
# Mirror of: backend/.ai-context | Owner: Siddhesh (Architect + Dev)

## STACK (NO DEVIATIONS)
Framework:    React 18 + Vite
Styling:      Tailwind CSS ONLY
              → No other CSS framework. No CSS modules. No styled-components.
State:        useState + useContext ONLY
              → No Redux. No Zustand. No Jotai. No Recoil.
Routing:      React Router v6 (useNavigate, useParams only)
HTTP:         Fetch API only (built into browser)
              → No axios. No react-query. No SWR.
Icons:        Lucide React (already installed)
Animations:   CSS transitions + Tailwind animate classes only
              → No Framer Motion unless Siddhesh explicitly adds it.

## WHAT AI CANNOT DO
→ Install any library not listed above
→ Use localStorage or sessionStorage — EVER
→ Create files outside /src folder structure below
→ Use class components — functional + hooks only
→ Add inline styles (style={{...}}) unless Tailwind can't do it
→ Suggest architectural changes after 3AM Mar 27
→ Use any <form> tag — use onSubmit on divs or onClick on buttons
→ Import from paths that don't exist yet — create the file first

## FOLDER STRUCTURE (DO NOT DEVIATE)
/src
  /api
    client.js         ← ALL fetch calls. One function per endpoint. Siddhesh owns this.
  /hooks
    useApi.js         ← Custom React hooks wrapping api/client.js
  /context
    AppContext.jsx    ← Global state (items list, active view, PS-specific state)
  /components
    UploadPanel.jsx   ← Text / Audio / File upload — generic, reusable
    DataCard.jsx      ← Renders any JSON item from Supabase as a card
    DataGallery.jsx   ← List/grid of DataCards, handles empty + loading
    /ui
      LoadingState.jsx  ← Spinner + skeleton variants
      ErrorState.jsx    ← Error display with retry button
      StatusBadge.jsx   ← Generic colored badge (severity, type, status)
  /pages
    HomePage.jsx      ← Default landing — will be reskinned per PS

## BACKEND CONTRACT (READ-ONLY — DO NOT MODIFY BACKEND)
Base URL:   import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL  (e.g. http://localhost:8000)
Endpoints:
  POST /api/process-text    body: { text: string, prompt_type: string }
                            returns: Item (id, type, content{}, metadata{}, created_at)
  POST /api/process-audio   body: FormData { audio: File, prompt_type: string }
                            returns: { transcript: string, item: Item }
  POST /api/process-image   body: FormData { image: File }
                            returns: Item
  POST /api/generate        body: { prompt: string }
                            returns: { result: string }
  GET  /api/items           returns: { items: Item[], count: number }
  POST /api/items           body: { type: string, content: {}, metadata: {} }
                            returns: Item
  GET  /health              returns: { status: "ok" }

Item shape:
  {
    id: string (uuid),
    type: string,
    content: Record<string, any>,   ← JSONB — structure varies per PS
    metadata: Record<string, any>,  ← JSONB — source, prompt_type, transcript, etc.
    created_at: string (ISO 8601)
  }

## ERROR HANDLING CONTRACT
Every API call must handle:
  → Network failure (fetch throws)
  → HTTP 4xx/5xx (response.ok === false)
  → { error: string } in response body (backend error format)
  → Timeout (no response after 30s)
Pattern: use the useApi hook — it returns { data, loading, error, execute }

