PRIMARY_USER:
CORE_FEATURE:
HERO_COMPONENT:       ← Which component is the demo money shot
COLOR_THEME:          ← e.g. "green/earth tones", "blue/civic", "amber/warm"
AUDIO_NEEDED:         ← yes/no (drives whether UploadPanel shows mic tab)

## COMPONENT RULES
DataCard.jsx:
  → Accepts any item object. Never hardcodes field names.
  → Renders content keys as labeled rows. Unknown keys → raw JSON fallback.
  → Has a "type" badge top-right using StatusBadge.

UploadPanel.jsx:
  → Three tabs: Text | Audio | File
  → Active tabs controlled by AUDIO_NEEDED and FILE_NEEDED flags
  → On submit → calls correct api/client.js function → shows LoadingState
  → On success → calls onSuccess(item) prop → parent decides what to do with result

DataGallery.jsx:
  → Accepts items[], loading, error props
  → Empty state: icon + "No items yet" message
  → Loading state: 3 skeleton DataCard placeholders
  → Error state: ErrorState component with retry button

## TAILWIND CONVENTIONS
→ Use semantic color classes: text-gray-900, bg-white, border-gray-200
→ Dark text on light backgrounds — no dark mode unless PS needs it
→ Responsive: mobile-first. Use sm: md: lg: prefixes.
→ Interactive elements: hover:bg-X focus:ring-2 focus:ring-X focus:outline-none
→ Spacing: use 4/8/12/16/24 multiples (Tailwind's scale)

## SECURITY
→ Never log response data to console (no console.log(data))
→ Never display raw API keys anywhere in UI
→ All user input trimmed before sending to API
→ File uploads: check file type client-side before sending (MIME check)
→ Audio: max 10MB client-side check before upload (backend also checks)

## GIT RULES (Bishnupriya read this)
→ Work only in /src/components — never touch /src/api or /src/hooks
→ One component per commit. Commit message: "feat: ComponentName — what it does"
→ If Siddhesh's files change, git pull before starting your task
→ Never push directly to main — push to feature/your-name branch

## DEMO REQUIREMENTS (Sakshi read this)
→ All loading states must be visible for at least 500ms (fake delay if needed)
→ No console errors on demo flow
→ All text must be readable at 1080p projected screen
→ Mobile layout must not break (judges may check phones)
